criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion criteria:

          -  Patient aged over six years, with primary lymphedema, regardless of the severity of
             the disease;

          -  Patient treated in one of the centres participating in the study;

          -  Patient (and her legal representative for minors) who gave her written consent [or did
             not refuse to participate, according to local Law];

          -  Patient with Internet access and an active email address.

        Exclusion criteria:

          -  Patients with concomitant chronic venous insufficiency;

          -  Patient not covered by any health care insurance scheme;

          -  People protected under the law.
